main event: On July 28, 1962, a civilian reported a sighting of a tear-drop shaped object hovering silently in Cuming County, Nebraska.
interesting points: The object was described as ultra-violet in color and emitted no sound.,Witness observed the object for approximately 15-20 seconds before it vanished.,No physical evidence was reported to substantiate the sighting.,The conclusion drawn was that it was a probable plasma phenomenon rather than an extraterrestrial craft.,There were no other confirmed witnesses to this event.
witness description: A civilian who perceived the object as a unique aerial phenomenon.
